[20]
. This weakening of hydrogen-surface bonding at the first layer of Pt is consistent with the chemisorptive properties of the Pt0.5Ni0.5 (1 1 1) alloys where it has not been possible to detect any adsorption except CO
[21]
,
[22]
. In this respect, the first Pt overlayer represents suitably a model surface of alloys showing particular properties quite different from those of bulk Pt.
